00:18:03,329 --> 00:18:06,096
That means Ryoga knows when
Ranma's going to strike.

262
00:18:06,196 --> 00:18:08,196
Well, after all
that, does this mean

263
00:18:08,296 --> 00:18:10,596
Ryoga's our new brother-in-law.

264
00:18:10,696 --> 00:18:12,629
Yes, I guess it does.

265
00:18:12,729 --> 00:18:14,496
I've had it.

266
00:18:14,596 --> 00:18:17,463
[screaming]

267
00:18:26,796 --> 00:18:28,329
SAOTOME (VOICEOVER):
Forgive me, Ranma.

268
00:18:28,429 --> 00:18:30,463
But I need someone
who won't lose focus

269
00:18:30,563 --> 00:18:32,863
on his job with family problems.

270
00:18:32,963 --> 00:18:35,429
Oh, sure, I remember how
hard we trained together

271
00:18:35,529 --> 00:18:37,963
as I groomed you to take
over the Saotome school.

272
00:18:48,563 --> 00:18:49,529
Goodbye, Ranma.

273
00:18:55,763 --> 00:18:58,329
What does he think he's doing?

274
00:18:58,429 --> 00:19:01,463
This announcer has no
idea what's going on here.

275
00:19:04,496 --> 00:19:05,363
Huh?

276
00:19:05,463 --> 00:19:07,796
Huh?

277
00:19:07,896 --> 00:19:11,696
[screaming] I hate cats!

278
00:19:11,796 --> 00:19:12,696
I hate 'em!

279
00:19:16,863 --> 00:19:18,663
Please tell me this
isn't the major weakness

280
00:19:18,763 --> 00:19:21,063
of Ranma's the master was
going to tell me about.

281
00:19:21,163 --> 00:19:22,963
This is so pathetic.

282
00:19:23,063 --> 00:19:24,996
Here's your big chance, Ryoga.

283
00:19:25,096 --> 00:19:27,796
This might be your
last opportunity, boy.

284
00:19:27,896 --> 00:19:31,296
It's time to get revenge for
Ranma stealing my sweets.

285
00:19:31,396 --> 00:19:32,263
Do it!

286
00:19:38,229 --> 00:19:40,629
What did you say?

287
00:19:40,729 --> 00:19:42,963
Your revenge for your
sweets being stolen?

288
00:19:46,663 --> 00:19:50,729
This was about you
getting your revenge?

289
00:19:50,829 --> 00:19:52,829
Why don't you
explain to everyone

290
00:19:52,929 --> 00:19:56,896
how you could do this do your
own son over some stupid sweets

291
00:19:56,996 --> 00:19:58,529
you had stashed away.

292
00:19:58,629 --> 00:20:01,163
Tell us, Saotome, is what
Ranma's saying the truth?

293
00:20:05,296 --> 00:20:07,063
This is all a misunderstanding.

294
00:20:07,163 --> 00:20:08,696
Misunderstanding?

295
00:20:08,796 --> 00:20:10,529
Ranma, you've
got to believe me.

296
00:20:10,629 --> 00:20:12,329
I was just training
Ryoga so that you

297
00:20:12,429 --> 00:20:15,063
could have a more equal
partner to work out with.

298
00:20:15,163 --> 00:20:17,796
You can't very well blame
you for that, now, can you?

299
00:20:17,896 --> 00:20:20,429
How can you stand
there and lie like that?

300
00:20:20,529 --> 00:20:21,829
OK, I admit it.

301
00:20:21,929 --> 00:20:24,263
I was just trying to teach you
a lesson for stealing my sweets.

302
00:20:24,363 --> 00:20:25,996
Now, back off!

303
00:20:26,096 --> 00:20:27,229
RYOGA: So Ranma's right.

304
00:20:27,329 --> 00:20:28,263
Huh?

305
00:20:28,363 --> 00:20:30,829
You were just using
me, weren't you?

306
00:20:30,929 --> 00:20:31,529
SAOTOME: No.

307
00:20:31,629 --> 00:20:32,663
How can you say that?

308
00:20:32,763 --> 00:20:34,796
Why, you've always been
like a son to me, Ryoga.

309
00:20:34,896 --> 00:20:40,163
And besides, why would
I lie? (LAUGHING)

310
00:20:43,729 --> 00:20:44,629
Help me!

311
00:20:54,163 --> 00:20:57,496
AKANE: Ranma, I
brought you some tea.

312
00:20:57,596 --> 00:21:00,229
There ain't no way
in a million years

313
00:21:00,329 --> 00:21:04,863
I'm ever going to forgive
Pop for what he did to me.

314
00:21:04,963 --> 00:21:07,663
Akane, did you happen to bring
those sweets I asked for.

315
00:21:09,863 --> 00:21:12,429
No, I think we're
all out of them.

316
00:21:18,829 --> 00:21:21,029
Doesn't she realize this is
how the whole mess started

317
00:21:21,129 --> 00:21:22,429
in the first place?

318
00:21:22,529 --> 00:21:25,696
Would somebody please tell me
why all this weird stuff always

319
00:21:25,796 --> 00:21:26,663
happens to me.

320
00:21:31,096 --> 00:21:34,063
Ah, Ranma, I see
you're becoming more

321
00:21:34,163 --> 00:21:36,063
like your old man every day.

322
00:21:41,129 --> 00:21:43,529
[theme music]

323
00:22:02,063 --> 00:22:04,529
[singing in japanese]

324
00:23:15,629 --> 00:23:17,263
NARRATOR: The residents
of the Tendo Dojo

325
00:23:17,363 --> 00:23:19,663
go to the amusement park,
only to find that there's

326
00:23:19,763 --> 00:23:21,496
no lunch, or any money.

327
00:23:21,596 --> 00:23:22,963
Now, what do we do?

328
00:23:23,063 --> 00:23:25,496
Next time on "Ranma
1/2," Tendo family

329
00:23:25,596 --> 00:23:26,829
goes to the amusement park.

330
00:23:26,929 --> 00:23:30,429
We'll see you there.

